WEBVTT

cue-1
00:00:00.099 --> 00:00:05.719
We use comparative adjectives to compare
two people, places, or things.

cue-2
00:00:06.188 --> 00:00:09.783
They tell us how one thing is different
from another.

cue-3
00:00:10.286 --> 00:00:18.293
For example, in a singular comparison, we
can say, "My dog is faster than your cat."

cue-4
00:00:18.608 --> 00:00:24.202
We can also use them to compare
groups of people, places, or things. 

cue-5
00:00:24.392 --> 00:00:31.321
For instance, in a plural comparison, 
we can say, "Dogs are faster than cats."
